            <title>[GROOVY-1023] methods with varargs are called with null when args are empty but should use an empty Array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1023</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;from VarargsMethodTest:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    void testVarargsOnly() &lt;/p&gt;
{
        assertEquals 0, varargsOnlyMethod() // todo: fix. throws NPE
    }
&lt;p&gt;    Integer varargsOnlyMethod(Object[] args) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        return args.size()
    }</description>
