For more informations, see&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy?cs=MAIN:phk:20050822032059&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy?cs=MAIN:phk:20050822032059&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461422" author="codevise" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 03:34:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t understand that the issue is closed with &quot;won&apos;t fix&quot; while the testcases still contains &quot;todo &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1023&quot; title=&quot;methods with varargs are called with null when args are empty but should use an empty Array&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-1023&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-1023&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
If &quot;won&apos;t fix&quot; means that null is the intended behavior, then the todos should be removed. Otherwise the issue should be kept open.&lt;br/&gt;
cheers Mittie&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461405" author="blackdrag" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 06:45:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;an example from java 5:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;public class Test {&lt;br/&gt;
	static void foo(int... i){}&lt;br/&gt;
	public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception&lt;/p&gt;
{
		assert foo(),0;
	}
&lt;p&gt;}&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I think groovy should behave the same way here! null is wrong (I forgot to test the cases with no arguments &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; )&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461343" author="phkim" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 09:32:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Dierk and Jochen &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If it is a bug not a feature, then you can (or should) fix it and commit the patch yourself, doesn&apos;t it ? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461445" author="meling" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 12:35:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this issue related to the quite serious bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1026&quot; title=&quot;Null argument to methods with vararg parameters are replaced with array of length 1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-1026&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-1026&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;??&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461467" author="phkim" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 12:37:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been fixed. Now the varargs feature when methods are invoked,&lt;br/&gt;
it works similary to the varargs feature of Java 5.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For details, see&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/groovy/groovy-core?cs=MAIN:phk:20050822173426&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://cvs.groovy.codehaus.org/changelog/groovy/groovy/groovy-core?cs=MAIN:phk:20050822173426&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14461482" author="phkim" created="Mon, 22 Aug 2005 12:53:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;These is related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1026&quot; title=&quot;Null argument to methods with vararg parameters are replaced with array of length 1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-1026&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-1026&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
